Skip Image Carousel Jupiter Country Club Who We Are Golf Amenities Host An Event Contact Us Transform Your Lifestyle with Membership at Jupiter Country Club Discover a new era of luxury and leisure at Jupiter Country Club. Experience our Greg Norman Signature golf course, world-class racquet sports, swimming, and a variety of dining options for every occasion. Coming in 2025: A brand-new, state-of-the-art fitness center featuring Technogym equipment, a Reformer Pilates studio, an indoor turf area, and more—designed to elevate your wellness journey. With a welcoming atmosphere and vibrant social events, Jupiter Country Club is the perfect place to connect, unwind, and make lasting memories. Contact Us To Learn More Membership Categories All memberships include a primary member, secondary member and any dependent under the age of 23. Learn More Full Golf More Details about Full Golf Full Golf Close Full access to all golf, tennis, pickleball, bocce, basketball, wellness, swimming, children's play area and dining and social facilities at the Club. Members enjoy 10-day advance tee time privileges, a private golf cart program and XLife benefits in the area and nationwide. Associate Golf More Details about Associate Golf Associate Golf Close Golf privileges are available after 12pm year-round. Full access to all tennis, pickleball, bocce, basketball, wellness, swimming, children's play area and dining and social facilities at the Club. Members enjoy 7-day advance tee time privileges, a private golf cart program and XLife benefits in the area and nationwide. Social More Details about Social Social Close Full access to all tennis, pickleball, bocce, basketball, wellness, swimming, children's play area and dining and social facilities at the Club. Members may upgrade to XLife benefits in the area and nationwide. Wherever you go, your membership goes, too. While our Club is exclusively open to Members and their guests, our Members have special access and opportunities at many other top-tier country clubs and golf courses in the area and nationwide through our relationship to the Invited Network. Wherever you go, your membership goes with you. Learn More

Refer A Member Refer your friends and family for Membership at Jupiter Country Club. Refer A Member Today! Beth Gili Membership Director Contact Me 561-576-6899 Contact Me About Beth + Close Beth Gili information modal Beth Gili Membership Director Serving since 2016 561-576-6899 Beth.Gili 561-576-6899 Beth.Gili Contact Me About Beth Born and raised in Clearwater, Florida, Beth has always cherished her state's vibrant culture and natural beauty. She earned a BS in Business Management with a Minor in Hospitality and Tourism Management from Florida Atlantic University (FAU) before joining JCC in 2016. Starting in Food & Beverage, Beth quickly excelled, moving to Office Manager/Accounting in 2021 and now serves as Membership Director, enhancing community spirit at JCC. A true Floridian, Beth loves soaking up the sun, hitting the beach, and going to sporting events, but her greatest joy is spending time with her dogs. Contact Me Hold on, there's more... • Love teeing off during your travels? • Enjoy discounts when you dine? Get all of this and more with XLife. Skip Image Carousel Meetings & Events Tournaments & Outings Making Memories at Jupiter Country Club Whether you're a Member or not, you're welcome to host your next event with us! Surrounded by a lush tropical landscape, Jupiter Country Club is the perfect venue to host your Palm Beach event. Whether you are planning a private social gathering or a professional meeting, our staff will ensure that you have everything you need to host an exceptional event. Our clubhouse can accommodate up to 80 guests for a wedding or 200 for a cocktail reception, and we welcome you to enjoy it on your special day. Contact Our Food & Beverage Director Create Unforgettable Private Events Host your next celebration at Jupiter and enjoy effortless planning with our dedicated team by your side. From intimate birthday dinners to lively pool parties, graduation celebrations, and anniversary gatherings, we handle every detail so you can relax and fully enjoy your special occasion. Let us help you craft an event that’s memorable from start to finish. Start Planning Your Event Host Inspiring & Productive Business Functions At Jupiter, we offer the perfect setting for corporate meetings and events. With customized service and top-notch facilities, we ensure your business gatherings are seamless and successful. Whether you're aiming to spark creativity, boost collaboration, or leave a lasting impression on your colleagues, we’ve got everything you need to elevate your next event. Schedule A Meeting Skip Content Carousel Extraordinary Jupiter Tournaments Entertain your colleagues with a golf outing, put together a tournament for fun, coordinate a groom's golf outing, host your charity’s fundraising tournament, play golf after your next meeting and more. The possibilities are endless. From our amazing golf course to the presentation of the food, service and elegant atmosphere, Jupiter is the perfect location for your next golf outing. Explore Tournaments & Outings

About Frank
Before moving to South Florida in 1997, Frank lived in Michigan, where he was raised. He attended Michigan State University graduating with a Finance/Insurance degree. Frank began his Golf career in the early 90s and has been a Class A Member of the PGA of America for over 20 years. Frank became Head Golf Professional at PGA National Golf Club in 1997 where he worked for 8 years creating unforgettable golf experiences for all members and guests. From 2005-2014, Frank held the position of Director of Golf & Amenities at Frenchman’s Reserve in Palm Beach Gardens as well as serving as their Interim General Manager from 2014-2015. In 2016, Frank assumed the role of General Manager of Parkland Golf and Country Club. Frank brings with him a wealth of club knowledge, high energy and a leadership style that will be welcomed by the staff and members alike.

About Beth
Born and raised in Clearwater, Florida, Beth has always cherished her state's vibrant culture and natural beauty. She earned a BS in Business Management with a Minor in Hospitality and Tourism Management from Florida Atlantic University (FAU) before joining JCC in 2016. Starting in Food & Beverage, Beth quickly excelled, moving to Office Manager/Accounting in 2021 and now serves as Membership Director, enhancing community spirit at JCC. A true Floridian, Beth loves soaking up the sun, hitting the beach, and going to sporting events, but her greatest joy is spending time with her dogs.

Raised in upstate New York, Jason moved to South Florida in 1991.  He started his golf career as an assistant professional in Wellington, FL and played in many mini-tour events.  In 1997, he moved to an assistant position at Delray Dunes G&CC and started his association with the PGA, becoming a Class A Member of the PGA in 2000.  From 2005 to 2021 Jason held the position of PGA Director of Golf at Lost City Golf Club.  As a golf traditionalist with an understanding of the modern golf environment and industry, he values the rules and etiquette of the sport but believe in adapting to the next generation.  Jason is TPI Certified for both Golf Instruction and Junior Golf.  He has served as a past director of our South Florida PGA Section and Chapter, and consistently offers services to the South Florida PGA programs such as the PGA H.O.P.E. program and PGA Junior Golf.

About Heinrich
Born and raised in Cape Town, South Africa, Heinrich’s early career includes working at Admirals Cove Country Club during the 2004-2005 season. Heinrich relocated to the United States in 2005 and joined the Toll Brothers team at Frenchman's Reserve Country Club. In 2008 he assisted with the opening of the Sports Club Facility at Jupiter Country Club & then returned to Frenchman’s Reserve Country Club to assist with opening “Parc” in 2010. In 2012 Heinrich moved to New Jersey & brought his Food & Beverage expertise to Spring Lake Golf Club. In May 2013 Heinrich joined the Parkland Golf and Country Club team as the Food and Beverage Director and was promoted in November 2018 to Golf Clubhouse Manager while at Parkland he was instrumental in creating a world-class wine program.
